<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,366,572]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
New record for 
<collectingCountry box="[361,483,398,419]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
. The aedeagus of this form is identical to that of 
<taxonomicName box="[981,1141,397,419]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foochowense">
<emphasis box="[981,1141,397,419]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">B. foochowense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and shares with that species several other characters (Luca Toledano, pers. comm), but is paler in colouration. This is the first record of this very distinctive group of the genus in 
<collectingCountry box="[387,511,459,480]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
. Specimens were identified by Luca Toledano. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lindroth" box="[1011,1176,458,480]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" refString="Lindroth, H. (1980) A revisionary study of the taxon Cillenus Samouelle, 1819 and related forms (Coleoptera: Carabidae: Bembidiini). Entomologica Scandinavica, 11, 179 - 205. *" type="journal article" year="1980">
Lindroth (
<number box="[1116,1169,458,480]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" value="1980.0">1980</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
originally described this species from Fujian Province and has since been found in 
<collectingCountry box="[745,819,489,511]" name="Taiwan" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Toledano" box="[833,988,489,511]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" refString="Toledano, L. (2009) Notes on the Bembidiina of Taiwan with description of three new species (Coleoptera: Carabidae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae. 49 (2), 577 - 598" type="journal article" year="2009">
Toledano 
<number box="[936,988,489,511]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1002,1096,489,511]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Material</emphasis>
: 
<number box="[1110,1122,489,511]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" value="1.0">1</number>
ex. W.T.L., 
<date box="[1249,1313,489,511]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" value="2006-05-09">
<number box="[1249,1262,489,511]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" value="9.0">9</number>
.v.06
</date>
; 
<number box="[1325,1337,489,511]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" value="1.0">1</number>
ex. W.T., 
<date box="[151,257,520,542]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" value="2011-06">
June 
<number box="[204,257,520,542]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</date>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[267,349,520,542]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Biology</emphasis>
: Imago found May to June. Species of this genus are renowned for living in the inter-tidal zone, especially at the sandy mouths of rivers. Fully winged.
</paragraph>
